cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper deals with improving the performance of wireless networks, specifically WLANs, through the use of multiple interfaces. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the security implications of using multiple WLANs, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper uses a Markovian model to analyze the network dynamics, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact on file transfer time, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
